
[1]perpetually

   PERPET'UALLY, adv. Constantly; continually; applied to things which
   proceed without intermission, or which occur frequently or at
   intervals, without limitation. A perennial spring flows perpetually;
   the weather varies perpetually.

   The Bible and common prayer book in the vulgar tongue, being
   perpetually read in churches, have proved a kind of standard for
   language.
